               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus private letter from Egypt in which Helias (Elias) requests information from Amones regarding an amount of solidi, gold coins. Mentions a monastery. Recto has a documentary text in Coptic (P.Duk.inv. 470 R)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 12.4 x 10.9 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">14 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1 cm.; lower margin(?) of 1 cm.; left margin of 0.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 470 V was formerly P.Miss. 36 V</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the verso; the address written across the fibers on the recto; also written across the fibers on the recto in a different hand and inverse to the text on the verso</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="egy-Copt">In Coptic</textLang>
